==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Connature
<hw>Con*na"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Participation
in a common nature or character.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Connature</qex> was defined as likeness in kind between
either two changes in consciousness, or two states of consciousness.</q>
<rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

